\pard\nowidctlpar\sa120\ul\b Startup:\par
\ulnone\b0 QODBC runs as a full demo for the first 30 days. This mode allows you to read and write all QuickBooks data and reports with the only restriction being 20 writes per session.\par
\ul\b Troubleshooting Tips:\par
\ulnone\b0 After you have installed the product, start and minimize QuickBooks, then test the installation by clicking the icon for "QODBC Setup Screen" under the QODBC Driver for QuickBooks folder and click the button that says "Test Connection to QuickBooks". If you installation is proper, you will get a success message. Now you can use the driver as-is which will connect to the currently open QuickBooks company file, or you can create a Data Set Name (DSN) for your own data file and QuickBooks will operate in the background. The processes to connect with various application tools can be found in the QODBC Manual.\par
If at any time you get an ODBC connect error message it is typically because of the following:\par

\pard\nowidctlpar\fi-360\li720\sa120\tx720\'b7\tab QuickBooks is not installed on the machine you are using. Install it to fix the problem, as it is required to use the QODBC product.\par

\pard\nowidctlpar\fi-360\li720\sa120\'b7\tab Your version of QuickBooks has not been updated to the latest revision from Intuit.\par
\'b7\tab If you have prior versions of QuickBooks loaded on the machine attempting to use QODBC, you will get a connectivity error. See our FAQ page on the web for details.\par
\'b7\tab You may be using the Read-Only or the Read-Write version of the driver as a system service or as a web component. Only our Web/Server Edition works in this manner.\par

\pard\nowidctlpar\sa120 For troubleshooting, please use "QODBC Support Wizard". Start "QODBC Support Wizard" from the start menu and follow the instructions.\par
If "QODBC Support Wizard" is able to connect, QODBC is installed and configured correctly.\par
In case you are still not able to connect, please submit a support ticket using "QODBC Support Wizard".\par
\ul\b\par
Setup Help:\par
\ulnone\b0 Make sure you are running the latest build of QuickBooks with the latest updates applied before running this driver. To see what version you are running, press the CTRL-1 key (not the keypad 1) while running QuickBooks.\par
The first time you run this driver with your own company data (using Microsoft Access or our included VB Demo Program), you need to be running QuickBooks Pro on the machine at the same time, and you need to be logged in as Administrator. This is for security reasons. When the driver starts, QuickBooks will ask permission for the driver to access your QuickBooks data. Answer \ldblquote Always allow access\rdblquote  to these files and you will only need to do this once. If you want to modify the files, you will also need to choose \ldblquote Multi-User Mode\rdblquote  from the Files menu in QuickBooks to allow this. You will need to go through this process for each application with which you want to access QuickBooks data.\par
Also, if you have trouble launching our user manual document, you may need to install the Adobe Acrobat reader program. This can be downloaded from this web site for free:\par
{{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK http://www.adobe.com/products/acrobat/main.html }}{\fldrslt{http://www.adobe.com/products/acrobat/main.html\ul0\cf0}}}}\f0\fs18\par

\pard\nowidctlpar\ul\b\par
General Information:\par
\par
\ulnone\b0 If you have any problems with the date format, use this format for direct SQL calls to our driver:\par
\{d \lquote 2002-09-27\rquote\}\par
Date and time stamps use this format:\par
SELECT * FROM Customer WHERE TimeCreated = \{ts \lquote 1999-07-29 14:24:18.000\rquote\}\par
Use this format for Microsoft Access queries:\par
SELECT * FROM Invoice WHERE Invoice.TimeModified >= #2003-09-23 00:00:01#\par
The Access format may vary based on the setting for default date format in your Windows control panel.\par

